  "texts": [
    "However, GPT-4 appears to be well on the way to being able to write psychological papers virtually unaided (aside from prompting).",
    "Additionally, because we were able substantiate 73.8% of claims with external validation, an AI model trained using more school psychology specific literature would likely yield more accurate (unaided) output.",
    "We believe that the field of psychology needs to create clear guidelines for the use LLMs, such as GPT-4, for academic writing.",
    "Furthermore, professional organizations such as the American Psychological Association, and the National Association of School Psychologists need to discuss the possible impact of LLMs with their members.",
    "This should include guidance regarding ethical/legal concerns and the possible impact on job tasks."
